itemLabel: Wavell Wakefield, 1st Baron Wakefield of Kendal
itemDescription: English rugby union footballer, politician and Baron (1898-1983)

wikipedia_page.main: William Wavell Wakefield, 1st Baron Wakefield of Kendal (10 March 1898 – 12 August 1983), known as Sir Wavell Wakefield between 1944 and 1963, was an English rugby union player for Harlequins, Leicester Tigers and England, President of the Rugby Football Union and Conservative politician.
